All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Map<String,Object>
public final class StyleSetting
extends GenericJson

Represents a complete StyleSettings object. The primary key is a combination of the tableId and a styleId.

This is the Java data model class that specifies how to parse/serialize into the JSON that is transmitted over HTTP when working with the Fusion Tables API. For a detailed explanation see: http://code.google.com/p/google-api-java-client/wiki/Json

Author:
Google, Inc.

getKind

public String getKind()
Type name: an individual style setting. A StyleSetting contains the style defintions for points, lines, and polygons in a table. Since a table can have any one or all of them, a style definition can have point, line and polygon style definitions. The value returned may be null.

setResponseHeaders

public void setResponseHeaders(HttpHeaders responseHeaders)
Sets the HTTP headers returned with the server response, or null. This member should only be non-null if this object was the top level element of a response. For example, a request that returns a single StyleSetting would include the response headers, while a request which returns an array of StyleSetting, would have a non-null response header in the enclosing object only.
